orian" era="ce" normal="1843/1843">1843</unitdate><container id="aspace_f985b9849529041d8dc0f5a8ba7997f7" label="Mixed Materials [31924064940921]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_568f340246f63a50bcdbc9d331c5a88c" parent="aspace_f985b9849529041d8dc0f5a8ba7997f7" type="folder">17</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_62940ac2599d23a370b4b8062e2b46d4" level="item"><did><unittitle>Tompkins County Election Returns, Nov. 30, 1836-Nov. 22, 1848 . Folder contains returns for various town, county, state, and federal elections held during this period. Articles from <title>Ithaca Daily Chronicle</title> and <title>Ithaca Journal</title>.</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1836-11-30/1848-11-22" type="inclusive">Nov. 30, 1836-Nov. 22, 1848</unitdate><container id="aspace_cfe9a156995392cfc39b09adfd477b18" label="Mixed Materials [31924064940921]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_efc9ad2109dca4ad61ad3b5b60423f8d" parent="aspace_cfe9a156995392cfc39b09adfd477b18" type="folder">18</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_8a7f96942566fca8837cb11c0479e48f" level="item"><did><unittitle>Articles on slavery, abolition, and colonization, Apr. 5, 1837-Apr. 18, 1838. Folder contains assorted articles on the issues surrounding slavery. Articles from <title>Ithaca Daily Chronicle</title> and <title>The Ithaca Journal and Herald</title>.</unittitle><container id="aspace_f6474c379b1df7522f377ebd3d70c200" label="Mixed Materials [31924064940921]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_f2907d6f52d0aace0339fc544cf767b2" parent="aspace_f6474c379b1df7522f377ebd3d70c200" type="folder">19</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_1c38f12fd9778ac3db661a741f138526" level="item"><did><unittitle>Residents of Tompkins County call meeting to discuss fiscal problems they believe caused by politicians in Albany. Article appears in May 7, 1834 <title>Ithaca Daily Chronicle</title>.</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1834-05-07/1834-05-